-- Nalco to Complete Indonesian Coal Deal by January, ET Says
-- B y   M a d e l e n e   P e a r s o n
-- 2010-10-03T02:50:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-03/nalco-to-complete-indonesian-coal-deal-by-january-et-says.html
India’s state-owned National
Aluminium Co. will complete a deal with coal suppliers in
Indonesia by January to provide fuel for its $4 billion aluminum
project in that country, the Economic Times newspaper reported,
citing B.L. Bagra, the company’s director of finance.  MEC Coal, Bumi Murau Coal, Energy Indonesia and Pram Dwi
Jaya are the four companies that have tenders to supply the
coal, the report said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Madelene Pearson in Mumbai at 
 mpearson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jim McDonald at 
 jmcdonald8@bloomberg.net  